{{Politics of Somalia}}
'''Parliamentary elections''' were held in [[Somalia]] on 31 December 1984. The country was a [[one-party state]] at the time, with the [[Somali Revolutionary Socialist Party]] as the sole legal party. Voters were asked to approve a list of 171 SRSP candidates. Turnout was reported to be 99.86% by the [[Communist Somalia|communist government]].<ref>[http://www.ipu.org/parline-e/reports/arc/SOMALIA_1979_E.PDF Somalia] Inter-Parliamentary Union</ref>
